    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-01-14T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-01-14T11:00:00-05:00" n="292"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d292">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/18521: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stockholm</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-01-14T17:00:00+01:00"
                            >January 14, 1942—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received January 14—4:09 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>76. Helsinki’s 32, January 12, 3 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d292fn1">Not
                        printed.</note> German propaganda concerning Soviet plans for border states
                    also having noticeable effect in Sweden where fear and distrust of Russian aims
                    is scarcely less than in Finland. British Minister<note n="2" xml:id="d292fn2"
                        >V. A. L. Mallet.</note> has telegraphed his Government suggesting some
                    statement be made by Mr. Eden<note n="3" xml:id="d292fn3">Anthony Eden, British
                        Secretary of State for Foreign Affairs.</note> in House of Commons which
                    would allay apprehensions of the northern countries and that Soviets be pressed
                    to make some disavowal of aggressive intentions. Should our Government find it
                    possible publicly to make some <pb facs="0333" n="327" xml:id="pg_327"/>
                    contribution to the same end, would have immense value in strengthening support
                    here for cause of democracies in Government and public opinion.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Helsinki.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
